
---


@startuml

' Define classes
class Sensor {
  +vendorId: String
  +description: String
  +unit: String
  +room: Room
  +threshold: float
  +hasEmailAlert: boolean
  +getValues(): List<Value>
  +getLastValue(): Value
  +setThreshold(threshold: float)
  +setDescription(description: String)
  +setRoom(room: Room)
}

class Value {
  +timestamp: DateTime
  +value: float
  +sensor: Sensor
}

class Room {
  +description: String
  +sensors: List<Sensor>
}

class Apartment {
  +address: String
  +rooms: List<Room>
  +inhabitants: List<Inhabitant>
  +emailAddress: String
}

class Inhabitant {
  +username: String
  +password: String
  +isAdmin: boolean
  +apartment: Apartment
  +login(username: String, password: String): boolean
  +querySensorValues(sensor: Sensor): List<Value>
  +setThreshold(sensor: Sensor, threshold: float)
  +configureSensor(sensor: Sensor, description: String, room: Room)
}

class EMonitor {
  +checkThresholds(): void
  +sendAlertMessage(apartment: Apartment, message: String): void
}

' Relationships
Sensor "1" -- "1" Room: belongs to
Sensor "1" -- "0..*" Value: has
Apartment "1" -- "1" Inhabitant: belongs to
Apartment "1" -- "0..*" Room: contains
Inhabitant "1" -- "1" Apartment: resides in
EMonitor "1" -- "1" Apartment: monitors
EMonitor "1" -- "0..*" Sensor: checks thresholds of

@enduml

---

### 📌 **Explanation of Key Elements**

| Class        | Attributes & Operations                                                                 |
|--------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Sensor**   | vendorId, description, unit, room, threshold, hasEmailAlert, getValues(), getLastValue(), setThreshold(), setDescription(), setRoom() |
| **Value**    | timestamp, value, sensor                                                                 |
| **Room**     | description, sensors                                                                     |
| **Apartment**| address, rooms, inhabitants, emailAddress                                               |
| **Inhabitant**| username, password, isAdmin, apartment, login(), querySensorValues(), setThreshold(), configureSensor() |
| **EMonitor** | checkThresholds(), sendAlertMessage()                                                    |

---

### 🧾 **Relationships Summary**

- A **Sensor** belongs to a **Room**.
- A **Sensor** has multiple **Values**.
- An **Apartment** has multiple **Rooms**.
- An **Apartment** has multiple **Inhabitants**.
- An **Inhabitant** belongs to an **Apartment**.
- **EMonitor** monitors an **Apartment** and checks thresholds of **Sensors**.

